 focusing on attributes like `id`, `subject`, `client`, `priority`, `category`, and `status`. I'm mapping API responses to this structured format, ensuring consistent data representation and addressing potential null values. I've considered default fallback values for clarity in the UI.\n\n\n**Refining Ticket Handling**\n\nI'm now refining ticket handling, focusing on data mapping and error conditions. I'm mapping API responses to the ticket interface, adding default values to handle nulls and ensure data consistency in the UI. I've also implemented `useEffect` to trigger the `fetchData` function automatically when filters change, which is elegant. I've considered how to handle the \"create ticket\" functionality, and I'm investigating how it works.\n\n\n**Constructing Ticket Payload**\n\nI'm now constructing the payload for creating support tickets. I've integrated logic to retrieve the authentication token from `localStorage`. If it's absent, an error is thrown. I've also implemented client ID mapping, and included the ticket subject, client ID, priority, category, assigned agent, status, and description within the `payload` object. I am also working with related ticket attributes.\n\n\n**Implementing Status Updates**\n\nI've integrated the status update functionality. I've focused on using `localStorage` to retrieve the authentication token. I handle token absence by throwing an error. I've also implemented the PATCH request to `/api/v1/support/${id}/status`, including appropriate headers and the `status` in the request body. I'm handling the response, including error messages.\n\n\n**Implementing Agent Reassignment**\n\nI'm now incorporating agent reassignment. I'm building out a `handleAssignAgent` function that retrieves the authentication token. It then crafts a PATCH request to `/api/v1/support/${id}/assign`, including the agent's name in the payload. Upon a successful response, I refresh the ticket list, and display feedback. Otherwise, an error is shown.\n\n\n**Integrating Reply Functionality**\n\nI'm now integrating the reply functionality. I've successfully implemented the `handleSendMessage` function, which crafts a POST request to `/api/v1/support/[id]`. The request includes the message text in the payload and the user's authentication token. On a successful response, I will update the UI. Error handling is also implemented.\n\n\n**Managing UI States**\n\nI'm now focusing on managing UI states for loading, error, and empty ticket lists. I've updated the `app/admin/support/page.tsx` file to display a loading indicator if the `loading` state is true and the ticket list is empty. For errors, I'll integrate an error message display. For an empty list, I'll ensure a message guides the user. The idea is to enhance the user experience.\n\n\n**Handling Empty Ticket State**\n\nI'm now implementing the display for the empty ticket list state, using the provided UI markup. When there are no tickets after the data is filtered, a message and an appropriate icon will be displayed. I've integrated this directly into `app/admin/support/page.tsx`, and I'm ensuring it's shown instead of the ticket list if the filter produces an empty list. Error handling is also covered.\n\n\n**Designing Governance Page States**\n\nI'm now designing the governance page states, considering the loading, error, and empty states. I'm focusing on replicating the premium state management implemented in the support page. I've initiated the data loading using a similar `fetchData` function, and identified the `/api/v1/governance` endpoints with their corresponding filters. I'm implementing similar error handling and displaying a retry button.\n\n\n**Refactoring Authentication Logic**\n\nI'm now refactoring the `fetchData` function to optimize authentication. I'm focusing on consolidating token retrieval and login. I've streamlined the login process within `fetchData` to minimize redundant calls and handle authentication gracefully. If a token is not in `localStorage`, a login attempt is initiated with hardcoded credentials before making authenticated API requests. I've also integrated an updated `useEffect` to trigger `fetchData` based on dependency changes.\n\n\n**Optimizing Governance Fetch**\n\nI'm now optimizing the governance data fetching and filtering. I'm focusing on crafting the correct URL for fetching governance items, including parameters for client, severity, status, and search query filters. I'm taking the opportunity to incorporate logic that maps display client names to client IDs before constructing the URL, as well as conditional logic for each parameter. I'm also ensuring the API call is authenticated.\n\n\n**Refining Alert Mapping**\n\nI'm now refining the governance alert data mapping to ensure data integrity and user-friendliness. I've updated the mapping logic to handle potential null or undefined values. I'm focusing on providing more descriptive defaults for key fields, like the client and project, by leveraging fallback values and helper functions for better data representation. I am now incorporating default values, making the alert's format more robust.\n\n\n\n**Implementing Governance Updates**\n\nI'm now integrating governance item updates within `/admin/governance`. I've analyzed the API endpoint `/api/v1/governance/[id]` and confirmed it supports PATCH requests for updating owner and status. I've implemented a `handleApplyOverrides` function to manage these updates, utilizing `fetch` to send the PATCH request with the required payload. It incorporates similar error handling and feedback mechanisms as the support ticket updates.\n\n\n**Integrating Governance Updates**\n\nI've now finalized the integration of governance updates in the `/admin/governance` section. I've successfully implemented the `handleApplyOverrides` function, using the `fetch` API for making PATCH requests to `/api/v1/governance/[id]` with the new owner and status payloads. I'm handling the data by successfully navigating through errors in the governance updates. Upon successful update, I display a success toast, close the alert detail view and refresh the list. Error handling is also built-in.\n\n\n**Implementing Governance Creation**\n\nI'm now integrating the \"Create Governance Alert\" functionality. I'm focusing on adding a button and a modal for input. I've introduced state variables for the modal's open/close state, title, and client. I'll need to define the API endpoint and the payload structure, including client, severity, status, and description, for creating the alert.\n\n\n**Designing Creation Flow**\n\nI'm now designing the governance alert creation flow, and I am focused on the modal UI. I've defined the API endpoint and confirmed the required payload including client and title, and considered other fields. I'm focusing on incorporating client selection from a predefined list, which is: Apex Sovereign Group, Global Retail Enclave, Sovereign Logistics Unit, and Federal Treasury Division. I've also identified required input fields for title and description.\n\n\n**Implementing Creation Workflow**\n\nI'm now implementing the governance alert creation workflow based on the UI markup provided. I'm focusing on integrating the form submission, client selection, and input field handling, and I'm updating my `handleCreateGovernance` function to submit the form data to the backend. I'm integrating the correct API request for the creation, including error handling and updating the UI after a successful submission.\n\n\n**Finalizing Creation Implementation**\n\nI'm now finalizing the implementation of the \"Create Governance Alert\" functionality. I've finished integrating the UI markup with dynamic content, including the input fields for title and description, and the client selection dropdown. I've updated the `handleCreateGovernance` function to submit the form data to the backend. The API call is integrated with error handling and UI updates for seamless user experience.\n\n\n**Integrating Severity Updates**\n\nI'm now integrating severity updates into the alert creation. I am focusing on the `<select>` element to pick a severity option. I've successfully added options for 'Low', 'Medium', 'High', and 'Critical' severities to the component. I will update the `createGovernance` state based on selections in the UI. I am also implementing the project association section.\n\n\n**Adding Project Association**\n\nI'm now integrating the project association with governance alert creation. I'm focusing on the logic that is linked to the select options to associate an alert with its project. I'm taking the opportunity to handle updates in state. I've successfully added options to the project association and also the standard reference section to the UI. I will also incorporate an enclave node ID input field.\n\n\n**Finalizing Creation Implementation**\n\nI'm now finalizing the \"Create Governance Alert\" implementation, and integrating the project association, and enclave node ID. I've finished the UI component, and integrated the `createNodeId`, and incorporated the severities and project. The alert description and the title are also linked to state. I'm taking the opportunity to handle updates in state. The form is ready for data submission.\n\n\n**Refining Submission Logic**\n\nI'm now refining the governance alert submission logic. I've updated the `handleCreateGovernance` function to include the `severity`, `standard`, and `nodeId` in the API call. I'm focusing on ensuring these values, along with the other required fields, are correctly sent to the backend. The integration includes input sanitization.\n\n\n**Finalizing Creation Implementation**\n\nI'm now finalizing the \"Create Governance Alert\" implementation. I've successfully incorporated the `handleCreateGovernance` function to create alerts. I've updated the `createGovernance` to include the `severity`, `standard`, and `nodeId` in the API call. I'm focusing on handling data and API interaction, as well as error handling. I've also incorporated the input sanitization for a secure experience.\n\n\n**Designing Ledger States**\n\nI'm now integrating the loading, error, and empty states for the alert ledger within the `/admin/governance` page, based on the provided UI markup. Specifically, I'm updating the `page.tsx` file to incorporate loading, error, and empty states, replacing the basic conditional rendering with a more structured approach. I've designed the visual elements to indicate each state clearly, enhancing the user experience.\n\n\n**Implementing Ledger States**\n\nI'm now implementing the UI updates for loading, error, and empty states within the `/admin/governance` page's alert ledger. I've integrated the provided UI markup to display loading indicators, error messages with a retry button, and a message with an icon when the alert list is empty. These updates, integrated into `page.tsx`, ensure a more user-friendly experience when no alerts are displayed.\n\n\n"}}
